title: Prince and Princess of Wales surprise guests at Jordan royal wedding
description: The Prince and Princess of Wales have made a surprise visit to Jordan to attend the wedding of the country's Crown Prince and his Saudi Arabian bride.

title: Micro-needling and cupping therapy 'can increase certain desired effects on your skin'
description: Micro-needling and cupping therapy may aid skin rejuvenation, according to a new study.

title: 50 Cent announces new tour dates in Australia and New Zealand
description: 50 Cent has announced he will be going to Australia and New Zealand as part of his The Final Lap tour.

title: South Korea uses AI to 'weigh' Kim Jong Un
description: South Korean officials have used artificial intelligence to estimate the weight of North Korean leader Kim Jong Un.

title: Woman jailed for helping orchestrate attacks on neo-Nazis
description: A woman has been jailed for more than five years for helping orchestrate attacks on neo-Nazis and other right-wing extremists in Germany in a two-year period.

title: Man accused of robbing store using Nintendo Duck Hunt pistol
description: A man has been arrested over the armed robbery of a convenience store in which police said a Nintendo video game controller was used to threaten a shop worker into handing over $300 (£240).

title: New anti-LGBTQ+ law with powers to 'kill' defended by Uganda's president
description: Uganda has passed one of the world's harshest anti-LGBTQ+ laws in order to punish what the country's president calls "disorientated" members of the community who try to "recruit" others.

title: 'Callous and inhumane' ex-SAS soldier loses war crimes case in Australia
description: One of Australia's most decorated living war veterans has lost a defamation lawsuit against three newspapers which accused him of war crimes in Afghanistan.

title: Novak Djokovic accused of 'promoting Serbian propaganda' at French Open
description: Kosovo's Olympic Committee has urged authorities to open disciplinary proceedings against Novak Djokovic over his controversial message about the country.

title: Madeleine McCann: Police 'seized a number of items' in Portuguese reservoir search
description: Police investigating the disappearance of Madeleine McCann "seized a number of items" during last week's search operation in a Portuguese reservoir.

title: Kim Jong Un's sister vows North Korea will succeed in launching spy satellite
description: Kim Jong Un's sister has vowed North Korea will be successful in its efforts to launch a spy satellite  - after its most recent attempt ended in failure.
